* A class that aggregates connect() statistics.
 * {@hide}

variables.name: netId
variables.comment: Network id of the network associated with the event, or 0 if unspecified.

variables.name: transports
variables.comment: Transports of the network associated with the event, as defined in NetworkCapabilities.

variables.name: errnos
variables.comment: How many events resulted in a given errno.

variables.name: latencies
variables.comment: Latencies of successful blocking connects. TODO: add non-blocking connects latencies.

variables.name: mLatencyTb
variables.comment: TokenBucket for rate limiting latency recording.

variables.name: mMaxLatencyRecords
variables.comment: Maximum number of latency values recorded.

variables.name: connectBlockingCount
variables.comment: Total count of successful connects done in blocking mode.

variables.name: ipv6ConnectCount
variables.comment: Total count of successful connects with IPv6 socket address.

methods.name: boolean addEvent(int errno, int latencyMs, String ipAddr)
private void countConnect(int errno, String ipAddr)
private void countLatency(int errno, int ms)
